<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-279] Allow specialization of quorum config parsing (e.g. variable expansion in zoo.cfg)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-279</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We would like to define certain parts of ZooKeeper&apos;s configuration using variables that get substituted. For example, we want the ZooKeeper quorum to be able to use a dataDir configured per user. In other words, something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;tickTime=2000&lt;br/&gt;
dataDir=/tmp/zookeeper-$&lt;/p&gt;
{user.name}
&lt;p&gt;clientPort=2181&lt;br/&gt;
initLimit=5&lt;br/&gt;
syncLimit=2&lt;br/&gt;
server.1=zoo1:2888:3888&lt;br/&gt;
server.2=zoo2:2888:3888&lt;br/&gt;
server.3=zoo3:2888:3888&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think Java already has a system for configuration that allows something like this using Properties?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
